relationship
with President Trump, after some
tension during

10:07.474 --> 10:08.441 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the campaign.

10:08.475 --> 10:09.676 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:09.709 --> 10:10.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: We're
doing fine.

10:10.944 --> 10:14.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're getting along very well,
speak fairly
frequently.

10:14.881 --> 10:16.549 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mike is coming up for lunch
today.

10:16.583 --> 10:19.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we have spent a lot of time
together coordinating
our strategy.

10:19.185 --> 10:20.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The vice
president.

10:20.186 --> 10:21.154 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:21.187 --> 10:22.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, the vice
president.

10:22.188 --> 10:23.990 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we get along very well.

10:24.023 --> 10:25.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, you speak
often, but do
they consult you not just on the
routine things

10:25.959 --> 10:31.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like the legislative calendar,
but, for example,
did you know ahead of time about
the immigration

10:31.130 --> 10:32.098 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ban?

10:32.131 --> 10:33.099 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:33.132 --> 10:34.901 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: On that one, I
didn't.

10:34.934 --> 10:37.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we have decided, on a
go-forward basis,
that we are going to have more
consulting

10:37.237 --> 10:40.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and make sure that no one's
caught by surprise
on things.

10:40.373 --> 10:44.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have basically mapped out
what 2017 looks
like from a legislative
perspective.

10:44.711 --> 10:45.678 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Already?

10:45.712 --> 10:46.679 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:46.713 --> 10:47.814 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL RYAN: Absolutely.

10:47.847 --> 10:48.681 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's what you do when you're
running a legislature.

10:48.715 --> 10:50.450 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You plan your year.

10:50.483 --> 10:55.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so Senator McConnell and I
walked the
president through basically what
we see 2017

10:55.955 --> 10:57.757 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
looking like.

10:57.790 --> 11:01.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And there is a lot of
deadline-driven events,
statutory deadlines that you
have to meet.

11:01.361 --> 11:04.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then there are plenty of
other priorities
that we're working on.

11:04.230 --> 11:10.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so just that planning
process gets you
talking about the big issues,
the big picture

11:10.370 --> 11:12.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and all the things we're trying
to get done
and when we're trying to get
them done.

11:13.006 --> 11:15.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I want to
stay with the
immigration ban for just a
moment, because

11:15.575 --> 11:18.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
former CIA Director Michael
Hayden, whom you
know...

11:19.012 --> 11:19.979 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

11:20.013 --> 11:21.748 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: I know Mike well,
yes.

11:21.781 --> 11:23.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: ... joined a
legal brief with
a number of other national
security experts

11:23.583 --> 11:27.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in saying that they not only
don't think this
is going to make the United
States safer,

11:27.921 --> 11:33.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they don't see a threat from
these seven countries,
but they think it could make the
country less

11:33.326 --> 11:37.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
safe, because it is going to be
easier to
attract people who want to work
with terrorist

11:37.130 --> 11:39.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
groups against the U.S., to say
the U.S. is
anti-Muslim.

11:39.832 --> 11:40.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

11:40.833 --> 11:41.801 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

11:41.834 --> 11:43.036 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
PAUL RYAN: Yes.

11:43.069 --> 11:44.671 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I think the rhetoric is
damaging, no two ways
about it.

11:44.704 --> 11:46.573 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's back up for a second.

11:46.606 --> 11:51.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After the Paris shooting, we
brought the Department
of Homeland Security and FBI up
to Capitol

11:51.511 --> 11:54.480 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hill to say, what is happening?

11:54.514 --> 11:56.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Could this happen here?

11:56.349 --> 11:59.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Because, if you remember, at the
Paris shooting,
there was an infiltration of
ISIS among the

11:59.619 --> 12:01.588 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syrian refugee population into
Europe.

12:01.621 --> 12:03.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But it turned out
there were
not refugees involved.

12:03.856 --> 12:04.857 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

12:04.891 --> 12:06.659 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: But that was the
issue at the time.

12:06.693 --> 12:09.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so what Homeland Security
and the FBI
told us was, they can't vet
these people.

12:09.662 --> 12:12.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There -- there isn't a Siri (ph)
to talk to,
to vet these people.

12:12.865 --> 12:18.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so what we discovered was,
there was a
hole in the vetting process to
guard against

12:18.771 --> 12:21.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people trying to infiltrate the
refugee population.

12:21.074 --> 12:25.645 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so that is why we passed
legislation then
about a year ago.

12:25.678 --> 12:27.847 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The bill passed the House, but
it got filibustered
in the Senate.

12:27.880 --> 12:29.782 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So it never actually went into
law.

12:29.816 --> 12:34.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we have been long on record
on a bipartisan
basis that we need to get these
vetting standards

12:34.187 --> 12:37.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
right and we need to take a
pause in these
programs to make sure that we
have the vetting

12:37.890 --> 12:39.692 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
standards right.

12:39.726 --> 12:42.962 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The reason these seven
countries, which were
identified by the Obama
administration, are

12:42.996 --> 12:49.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
listed is because we have a hard
time corroborating
the veracity of people's claims
coming from

12:49.168 --> 12:50.970 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
those countries.

12:51.004 --> 12:55.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those countries in particular,
we have a hard
time discerning who exactly
these people are

12:55.642 --> 12:57.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that are coming into the
country.

12:57.443 --> 13:03.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That is why it's totally
reasonable and rational
to have a pause in this program,
so that we

13:03.216 --> 13:07.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can update and upgrade our
vetting standards,
so that we can be better secured
to make sure

13:07.453 --> 13:09.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we don't have somebody
trying to infiltrate
the network.

13:09.956 --> 13:13.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But there haven't
been terrorist
incidents perpetrated by people
from these

13:13.259 --> 13:14.227 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
countries.

13:14.260 --> 13:15.228 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I mean, that's...

13:15.261 --> 13:16.729 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:16.763 --> 13:18.097 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: From these countries
or from -- through
the refugee population?

13:18.131 --> 13:20.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From these countries,
absolutely, from the
refugee population.

13:20.099 --> 13:21.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

13:21.100 --> 13:22.902 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:22.935 --> 13:25.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: But the point is we
know that ISIS
is trying to infiltrate refugee
populations.

13:25.371 --> 13:27.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is intelligence that has
already been
unclassified.

13:27.774 --> 13:30.710 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the question is, are we
doing everything
we need to guard against that?

13:30.743 --> 13:34.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The point -- I think you made a
good point,
though, which is, this isn't a
Muslim ban.

13:34.881 --> 13:37.016 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If it were, I would be opposed
to it.

13:37.050 --> 13:41.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the rhetoric surrounding it
makes it look
like it's a ban on a religion or
a religious

13:41.621 --> 13:42.922 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
test.

13:42.955 --> 13:45.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that rhetoric is
inflammatory
and doesn't help us.

13:45.992 --> 13:49.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that raises
the question,
because the president himself
and others around

13:49.362 --> 13:54.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
him have talked about -- they
have talked
about their preference for a
Muslim ban.

13:54.300 --> 13:55.234 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:55.268 --> 13:56.235 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, and I disagree
with that.

13:56.269 --> 13:57.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I disagree with that.

13:57.470 --> 13:58.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are you confident
that there
will not...

13:58.271 --> 13:59.639 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:59.672 --> 14:00.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: I disagree with it
now and I disagreed
with it then.

14:00.339 --> 14:01.307 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But that's not what this is.

14:01.340 --> 14:03.142 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I understand
that.

14:03.176 --> 14:04.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But my question is, are you
confident this
administration is not going in
the direction

14:04.243 --> 14:05.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ever of a Muslim ban?

14:05.545 --> 14:07.280 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

14:07.313 --> 14:08.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, because we will
-- we will
-- I and many others around here
would oppose

14:08.648 --> 14:10.249 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

14:10.283 --> 14:12.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A little bit more
about your
relationship with the White
House.

14:12.151 --> 14:17.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that you are good
friends with fellow
Wisconsinite Chief of Staff
Reince Priebus.

14:17.757 --> 14:18.725 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

14:18.758 --> 14:19.726 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: He's my constituent.

14:19.759 --> 14:21.594 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That's right.

14:21.627 --> 14:24.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My question is, how is your
relationship with
Steve Bannon, who, when he was
at Breitbart

14:24.897 --> 14:30.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
News, took a special interest in
you, called
you the enemy after you became
speaker?

14:30.870 --> 14:31.838 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

14:31.871 --> 14:32.839 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, I don't really
know him.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.640 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have gotten to know him two or
three times.

14:34.674 --> 14:35.641 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have had a few meetings.

14:35.675 --> 14:37.176 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have gotten along fine.

14:37.210 --> 14:39.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's not someone I have a
history with.

14:39.245 --> 14:44.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obviously, I didn't know him
when he was opposing
me all those times.

14:44.283 --> 14:45.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're different kinds of
conservatives.

14:45.418 --> 14:49.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's something I can safely
say, I think.

14:49.188 --> 14:51.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we're serving a purpose,
which is to get
this agenda passed.

14:52.024 --> 14:56.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on this agenda that we have
rolled out,
that we ran on, on that, we
agree.

14:56.496 --> 15:00.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I see a person in which I
have a common
cause and purpose with.

15:00.500 --> 15:02.135 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're different kinds of
conservatives.

15:02.168 --> 15:05.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We really don't know each other,
but we're
all trying to get this agenda
enacted.

15:05.271 --> 15:07.340 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's why I don't see a
problem here.

15:07.373 --> 15:09.308 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Russia.

15:09.342 --> 15:13.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have said on a number of
occasions you
want to see the sanctions
against Russia continued.

15:13.813 --> 15:17.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump, though, has
made some not
just conciliatory, but even
complimentary

15:17.517 --> 15:21.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
comments in the last few days
about President
Putin.

15:21.420 --> 15:22.388 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Were you shocked by that?

15:22.421 --> 15:23.389 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

15:23.422 --> 15:24.390 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, I just don't see
it that way.

15:24.423 --> 15:26.325 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I just see it differently.

15:26.359 --> 15:32.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, first of all, I don't
subscribe to
relativism, whether it's in
political philosophy,

15:32.698 --> 15:34.534 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
foreign policy or in life.

15:34.567 --> 15:38.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I don't think there is a
moral equivalency
here at all.

15:38.437 --> 15:41.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I just disagree with any
kind of notion
of a moral equivalency.

15:41.607 --> 15:47.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a gaping difference
between the United
States of America and Putin's
Russia.

15:47.246 --> 15:49.081 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's point number one.

15:49.115 --> 15:53.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Point number two, I think what
the president
is trying to do is not unlike
what the past

15:53.052 --> 15:54.420 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
two presidents did with Russia.

15:54.453 --> 15:56.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I just don't think it's going to
work.

15:57.023 --> 15:59.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Remember when George W. Bush
said I could
see through his soul or
something like that?

15:59.759 --> 16:00.726 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trying to get
close to Russia.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.495 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:02.528 --> 16:03.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, he was trying to
get close
to Russia and trying to get
close to Putin.

16:03.095 --> 16:04.330 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
George Bush did that.

16:04.363 --> 16:06.232 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't think it worked.

16:06.265 --> 16:10.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Remember Hillary Clinton with
the reset button
on behalf of Barack Obama,
trying to get close

16:10.169 --> 16:12.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Russia, trying to smooth
things out with
Russia?

16:12.872 --> 16:14.407 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
New administrations do this.

16:14.440 --> 16:17.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, it's logical as to why they
want to do
this.

16:17.810 --> 16:21.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are instances in which our
interests
align with Russia and there are
those where

16:21.647 --> 16:23.416 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
they don't.

16:23.449 --> 16:28.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so the question is, can we
help steer
Russia to being something that
doesn't conflict

16:28.054 --> 16:31.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with our interests and something
that -- and
a country that aligns with our
interests?

16:31.791 --> 16:33.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't personally -- I'm not
going to hold
my breath on that.

16:33.893 --> 16:37.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, if this
president were
to relax sanctions against
Russia...

16:37.396 --> 16:38.364 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:38.397 --> 16:39.732 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, I don't support
that.

16:39.765 --> 16:40.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: ... would you
support legislation
to prevent it?

16:40.666 --> 16:41.868 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:41.901 --> 16:43.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, no, I think the
advantages
were overdue.

16:43.936 --> 16:46.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think President Obama should
have done them
a year ago.

16:46.372 --> 16:48.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, you would
support legislation
to keep them strong?

16:48.741 --> 16:50.376 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:50.409 --> 16:52.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, I do support --
yes, I have
long supported sanctions on
Russia.

16:52.311 --> 16:57.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Turning domestic,
