cuts for 10 years.

18:44.523 --> 18:45.491 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

18:45.524 --> 18:46.492 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: That's to balance the
budget.

18:46.525 --> 18:47.493 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's not to pay for tax
reform.

18:47.526 --> 18:48.928 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I understand.

18:48.961 --> 18:50.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the public, the voters are
going to look
at this as connected.

18:50.896 --> 18:52.465 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

18:52.498 --> 18:54.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Yes, we have a budget
problem,
which is, we have a big budget
deficit.

18:54.367 --> 18:57.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we have a debt crisis in the
future because
of spending.

18:57.303 --> 19:01.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So you have to reduce spending
and reform
the spending programs in and of
themselves.

19:01.307 --> 19:03.209 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Put tax reform aside.

19:03.242 --> 19:05.044 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's no way -- it's
mathematical.

19:05.077 --> 19:09.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are not going to be able to
raise the kind
of tax revenues to chase the
kind of spending

19:09.148 --> 19:10.916 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that is coming in the future.

19:10.950 --> 19:14.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So you have to get spending
under control
if you're going to avert a debt
crisis down

19:14.720 --> 19:16.622 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the road.

19:16.655 --> 19:20.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
