is just so

19:46.519 --> 19:48.421 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
wrong.

19:48.454 --> 19:51.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think that was in reaction
to some suggesting
that we should sort of tinker
around the edges

19:51.891 --> 19:55.795 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and try and refine and repair
the existing
law.

19:55.828 --> 19:57.096 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is collapsing.

19:57.129 --> 19:59.165 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that's not viable.

19:59.198 --> 20:03.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so what we propose -- and we
ran on a
replacement plan, by the way.

20:03.502 --> 20:06.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we have had a -- long had a
replacement
plan for Obamacare.

20:06.772 --> 20:11.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's exactly what we're
focused on right
now is building a replacement
plan, so we

20:11.644 --> 20:16.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
repeal Obamacare and replace it
