20:41.640 --> 20:42.608 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

20:42.641 --> 20:43.609 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: Absolutely, yes.

20:43.642 --> 20:45.377 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have long supported...

20:45.411 --> 20:46.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Not something
called continuous
coverage, which isn't the same
thing?

20:46.212 --> 20:47.913 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

20:47.947 --> 20:50.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN: No, no, there's
different ways
of achieving preexisting
conditions reform.

20:50.349 --> 20:54.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We think Obamacare went about it
the exact
wrong way to guarantee that
people with preexisting

20:54.920 --> 20:57.690 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
conditions can get good
affordable coverage.

20:57.723 --> 21:02.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The goal here is, can people
with preexisting
-- can a woman who got breast
cancer when

21:02.361 --> 21:06.665 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
