39:35.273 --> 39:39.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I can see it in their eyes;
what they
really want to say is, aren't
you dead yet?

39:39.577 --> 39:41.346 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"Well, no.

39:41.379 --> 39:46.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As it turns out, I became a
terminal cancer
patient at a time of sea change
in research

39:47.018 --> 39:48.586 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on the disease.

39:48.620 --> 39:50.421 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What changed?

39:50.455 --> 39:55.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Immunotherapy, a new set of
medicines that
help patients like me use our
bodies' natural

39:55.293 --> 39:56.761 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
defenses to fight cancer."

39:56.794 --> 39:58.563 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

39:58.596 --> 40:02.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALAIN ALGAZI: Basically, there
are brake pedals
on immune cells, so when you
turn off the

40:02.233 --> 40:05.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
brake pedal, you allow the
immune system to
function, you allow it to fight.

40:05.436 --> 40:08.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think the cancer is always
there, and
it's a battle between the immune
system and

40:08.840 --> 40:10.508 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
