40:10.541 --> 40:13.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MELINDA WELSH: "Nobody knows how
long the
good news will last for me or
other cancer

40:13.411 --> 40:16.347 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
patients who are responding to
immunotherapy.

40:16.381 --> 40:22.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like me they probably feel a
miraculous gift
-- unanticipated time of unknown
duration

40:22.954 --> 40:25.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
-- has been dropped into their
laps."

40:25.156 --> 40:26.324 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

40:26.357 --> 40:28.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALAIN ALGAZI: It's like working
for NASA in
the 1960s.

40:29.027 --> 40:30.895 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You know, can you imagine?

40:30.928 --> 40:33.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That sense of discovery, that
